Text: L'Aigle à deux têtes is a French play in three acts by Jean Cocteau, written in 1943 and first performed in 1946.

Text: L'Aigle à deux têtes:  It is known variously in English as "The Eagle with Two Heads", "The Eagle Has Two Heads", "The Two-Headed Eagle", "The Double-Headed Eagle", and "Eagle Rampant".
